 Mo Abudu, a media entrepreneur and director, has slammed critics of her latest film, “Chief Daddy 2.” According to Kemi Filani News, the film has generated a wide range of emotions throughout social media since its January 1 premiere. In a recent development, Abudu issued a video on Friday, January 14th, 2022, in which she responded to the criticism. READ ALSO: Irrelevant And Successful People Stabbed Me In The Back’ – Mo Abudu While thanking viewers for their constructive feedback, the filmmaker stated that the company will not tolerate insults. See post below:   A post shared by Mo Abudu (@moabudu) 